Package: plotBayes
Title: Function for Exploring Bayesian Inference for the Sample Mean for Continuous Data
Version: 0.0.3
Authors@R: person("Matthew", "McBee", email = "mmcbee@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This function plots the prior, likelihood, and posterior distribution of the sample mean. It reports the MAP (maximum a posteriori, also called the posterior mode) and EAP (expected a posteriori) estimates of the mean.
Depends: R (>= 3.3.0)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
